## Key Highlights

Here are the key takeaways from this guide on understanding panic attacks:

- A panic attack is a sudden rush of intense fear with physical and mental symptoms.
- Common symptoms of a panic attack include a racing heartbeat, shortness of breath, and chest pain.
- Panic disorder is diagnosed when you have regular, unexpected attacks followed by a month of worry about future episodes.
- Effective treatment options, like therapy and medication, are available to manage your mental health.
- Self-help strategies and professional support can significantly improve your quality of life.

