## Frequently Asked Questions

### Can panic attacks be prevented, and how?

Yes, a panic attack can often be prevented. Prevention involves using self-help strategies like regular exercise, relaxation techniques, and avoiding triggers like caffeine. Therapy can also teach you coping skills to manage anxiety and improve your overall mental health. For expert guidance, consider reaching out to Riaz Counseling.

### What is the difference between panic disorder and anxiety attacks?

A panic attack is sudden and intense, while anxiety attacks (or general anxiety) tend to build more slowly. Panic disorder is diagnosed when you have recurring, unexpected attacks and live in fear of the next one. For help clarifying the symptoms of panic disorder, Riaz Counseling offers professional mental health support.

### How does therapy help manage panic attacks?

Therapy, especially cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT), helps you identify and change the negative thoughts and behaviors that fuel panic attacks. A therapist teaches you coping mechanisms and relaxation techniques to regain control. Riaz Counseling provides this kind of essential mental health support to help you manage your symptoms effectively.

